Ask HN: Why did they break Windows 11?
text:
Rant / I want to ask your experience.

There are so many breaking changes to Windows 11, especially to user interface which ruins power user's (or any user's) experience.

Some examples include: - Alt-Tab does not work like it used to; it's worse imo - Context menu is very different, less accessible - Folders behave differently - Task bar cannot "never combine" windows like why the hell would you remove features

I see so many breaking changes most of them without a way to revert, or need to go through burning hoops to change. most guides saying to change 10 options in registry often don't even work.

I miss Windows 7. I will even settle for 10 now...

Also I recommend reading this post about UI inconsistencies in Windows 11: https://ntdotdev.wordpress.com/2023/01/01/state-of-the-windows-how-many-layers-of-ui-inconsistencies-are-in-windows-11/

Ask HN: How to not get sucked into online discussions?
text: I am trying to learn to not reply to comments in online discussions. Especially, comments which are clearly wrong (imagine 2 + 2 = 5). So far, I have only been able to comment and then delete after a few minutes. Once I delete them, I feel much better; realizing other people's viewpoints are not my problem. I find replying to comments as negative to my mental health regardless whether I agree or disagree. I want to get to the point I can control the urge.
